> #### DNS Connections

Every time someone tries to connect in bastion sshd will call a node program and this process will capture as input parameter
a derivation of the private key in a public key, and from it all users and public keys (AWS CodeCommit) available at IAM panel are listed.
  The program then compares the public key with any of the keys listed, if exists is authenticated; and if not exists it's not authenticated.

> ##### DNS Bastion Name

  	bastion.[clustername].[region].devpanel.me
    ex:
  	bastion.cool7.us-east-2.devpanel.me

> ##### DNS RDS Name

  	rds.$clustername.$region.devpanel.me
    ex:
  	rds.cool7.us-east-2.devpanel.me

> #### SSH Access  

Create the keys and upload the public key at IAM.  
And access using the pattern "[user]:[site_cname]@access.[cluster_name].[region].devpanel.me".  
ps: at this release avoid use ssh tools that automaticlly try conect ftp too.
